What is Data ?
Ans : In simple words Data is collection of facts , such as
1. Numbers
2. Words
3. Measurements
4. Observations
 or we can also say, data is the name given to the basic facts and entities such
 as names and numbers
 examples:
 weight, price, no of items sold, employee names, product names, images, videos,
 sound, multimedia, symbols .

 Data Types in Python:
    1. Text Type : String
          Alphabets ( Text type -> String / str)
            A - Z
            a - z
          Special Characters ( Text type -> String / str)
            ! @ # $ % ^ & * ( ) < > ? / { } [ ]
    2. Numeric Types : int, float, complex
          Numbers ( Numeric Type )
            Non Decimal = 0, 1, 2, 3, .... 9     -> ( Integer / int )
            Decimal     = 0.1, 0.2, 0.6, .....   -> ( float )

    3. Boolean Type : True, False

    4. Sequence Type : list, tuple, range
    5. Mapping Type : dict
    6. Set Type : set, frozenset
    7. Binary Type: bytes, bytearray, memoryview







